name: Push-up
instructions: Start in a plank position, lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor, then push yourself back up.

name: Squat
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart, bend your knees, and lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then rise back up.

name: Deadlift
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart, bend at your hips and knees to lower your body and grab the bar, then lift it while keeping your back straight.

name: Pull-up
instructions: Hang from a bar with your palms facing away, then pull your body up until your chin is above the bar.

name: Plank
instructions: Hold your body in a straight line from head to heels, supported on your toes and forearms.

name: Lunge
instructions: Step forward with one leg, lower your hips until both knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle, then push back up.

name: Bicep Curl
instructions: Hold a dumbbell in each hand, curl the weights up to your shoulders, then lower them back down.

name: Bench Press
instructions: Lie on a bench, hold a barbell with hands slightly wider than shoulder-width, lower it to your chest, then push it back up.

name: Leg Press
instructions: Sit in the leg press machine, place your feet on the platform, and push it away from your body by extending your legs.

name: Shoulder Press
instructions: Hold dumbbells at shoulder height, press them overhead until your arms are fully extended, then lower them back down.

name: Tricep Dip
instructions: Sit on the edge of a bench, place your hands next to your hips, lower your body until your arms form a 90-degree angle, then push back up.

name: Russian Twist
instructions: Sit on the floor with knees bent, lean back slightly, rotate your torso to one side, then the other, while holding a weight.

name: Leg Raise
instructions: Lie on your back, lift your legs straight up towards the ceiling, then slowly lower them back down.

name: Mountain Climber
instructions: Start in a plank position, quickly alternate bringing one knee to your chest, then back out again, as if running in place.

name: Burpee
instructions: Start in a standing position, drop into a squat, kick your feet back into a plank, perform a push-up, return to squat, and jump up.

name: Box Jump
instructions: Stand in front of a sturdy box, jump onto the box, landing softly, then step back down.

name: Leg Curl
instructions: Lie face down on the leg curl machine, place your ankles under the pad, and curl your legs up towards your buttocks.

name: Crunch
instructions: Lie on your back with knees bent, place your hands behind your head, lift your shoulders off the floor, then lower them back down.

name: Chest Fly
instructions: Lie on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, open your arms wide, then bring the weights back together over your chest.

name: Lat Pulldown
instructions: Sit at a lat pulldown machine, grab the bar with a wide grip, pull it down to your chest, then slowly let it rise back up.

name: Calf Raise
instructions: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, lift your heels off the ground to stand on your toes, then slowly lower back down.

name: Glute Bridge
instructions: Lie on your back with knees bent, lift your hips towards the ceiling, squeeze your glutes, then lower back down.

name: Cable Row
instructions: Sit at a cable row machine, grab the handle, pull it towards your torso, keeping your back straight, then slowly release.

name: Face Pull
instructions: Attach a rope handle to a cable machine at face height, pull the handle towards your face, then slowly release.

name: Farmer's Walk
instructions: Hold a heavy weight in each hand, walk forward in a straight line, keeping your core tight and shoulders back.

name: Battle Rope
instructions: Hold the ends of a battle rope in each hand, make waves with the ropes by moving your arms up and down rapidly.

name: Kettlebell Swing
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart, hold a kettlebell with both hands, hinge at your hips to swing the kettlebell between your legs, then explosively swing it up to shoulder height.

name: Step-up
instructions: Stand in front of a bench or step, place one foot on the bench, push through your heel to stand up, then step back down.

name: Goblet Squat
instructions: Hold a dumbbell or kettlebell at chest height, squat down until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then stand back up.

name: Dumbbell Row
instructions: Place one knee and hand on a bench, hold a dumbbell in the other hand, row the weight up to your hip, then lower back down.

name: Chest Press
instructions: Lie on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, press the weights above your chest, then lower them back down.

name: Hip Thrust
instructions: Sit on the ground with your upper back against a bench, place a barbell over your hips, thrust your hips upwards, then lower them back down.

name: Arnold Press
instructions: Hold dumbbells at shoulder height with palms facing you, press them overhead while rotating your wrists so palms face forward at the top, then reverse the motion.

name: Barbell Row
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart, bend at your hips, hold a barbell, row the bar up to your torso, then lower it back down.

name: Skull Crusher
instructions: Lie on a bench, hold a barbell with arms extended, lower the bar towards your forehead, then extend your arms back up.

name: Hanging Leg Raise
instructions: Hang from a pull-up bar, lift your legs straight up towards the bar, then lower them back down.

name: Overhead Squat
instructions: Hold a barbell overhead with arms fully extended, squat down until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then stand back up.

name: Pistol Squat
instructions: Stand on one leg, lower your body into a squat while keeping the other leg extended in front of you, then stand back up.

name: Seated Calf Raise
instructions: Sit on a calf raise machine, place your knees under the pad, and lift your heels to raise the weight, then lower back down.

name: Single-leg Deadlift
instructions: Stand on one leg, hold a dumbbell in the opposite hand, hinge at your hips to lower the weight towards the ground, then stand back up.

name: Reverse Lunge
instructions: Step backward with one leg, lower your hips until both knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle, then push back up.

name: Renegade Row
instructions: Start in a plank position with a dumbbell in each hand, row one dumbbell towards your torso, then switch sides.

name: Side Plank
instructions: Lie on your side, support your body on your forearm and the side of your foot, hold the position, then switch sides.

name: Tire Flip
instructions: Squat down and grip the bottom of a large tire, lift it with your legs and hips, then flip it over.

name: Dragon Flag
instructions: Lie on a bench and hold onto it behind your head, lift your entire body up until only your upper back is on the bench, then slowly lower back down.

name: Hollow Body Hold
instructions: Lie on your back, lift your legs and shoulders off the ground, hold the position with your lower back pressed into the floor.

name: Jump Rope
instructions: Hold a jump rope in each hand, swing it over your head and under your feet, jumping as it passes under you.

name: Wall Sit
instructions: Stand with your back against a wall, slide down until your thighs are parallel to the floor, hold the position.

name: Windmill
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold a weight overhead, bend at the hips and lower your torso to one side, then stand back up.

name: Cable Crossover
instructions: Stand between two cable machines, hold a handle in each hand, bring the handles together in front of your chest, then slowly let them back out.

name: Inverted Row
instructions: Lie under a barbell set at waist height, grab the bar with an overhand grip, pull your chest to the bar, then lower back down.

name: Sled Push
instructions: Stand behind a weighted sled, lean into it with your arms extended, and push it forward as fast as you can.

name: Rope Climb
instructions: Grip a thick rope, use your arms and legs to climb it as high as possible.

name: Turkish Get-up
instructions: Lie on your back holding a kettlebell in one hand, stand up while keeping the kettlebell overhead, then lie back down.

name: Lateral Raise
instructions: Hold a dumbbell in each hand, raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, then lower them back down.

name: Reverse Fly
instructions: Hold a dumbbell in each hand, bend at the hips with a flat back, raise your arms out to the sides, then lower them back down.

name: Sledgehammer Slam
instructions: Hold a sledgehammer with both hands, swing it over your head and slam it onto a tire, then repeat.

name: Tuck Jump
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, jump as high as you can, bringing your knees to your chest, then land softly.

name: Medicine Ball Slam
instructions: Hold a medicine ball overhead, slam it into the ground as hard as you can, then catch it on the rebound.

name: Pallof Press
instructions: Stand next to a cable machine, hold the handle with both hands, press it straight out in front of you, resisting the rotation, then return to the starting position.

name: Overhead Tricep Extension
instructions: Hold a dumbbell with both hands behind your head, extend your arms to lift the weight overhead, then lower it back down.

name: Pendlay Row
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart, bend at your hips with a flat back, pull a barbell from the ground up to your torso, then lower it back down.

name: Dumbbell Pullover
instructions: Lie on a bench, hold a dumbbell with both hands above your chest, lower it behind your head, then bring it back up.

name: Romanian Deadlift
instructions: Hold a barbell with feet shoulder-width apart, hinge at your hips to lower the bar, keeping your back flat, then stand back up.

name: Barbell Curl
instructions: Hold a barbell with an underhand grip, curl it up to your shoulders, then lower it back down.

name: Landmine Press
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold the end of a barbell with both hands, press it overhead, then lower it back down.

name: Landmine Row
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold the end of a barbell with one hand, row it up to your torso, then lower it back down.

name: Zercher Squat
instructions: Hold a barbell in the crook of your elbows, squat down until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then stand back up.

name: Sissy Squat
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, lean back and lower your body by bending your knees, then stand back up.

name: Sumo Deadlift
instructions: Stand with feet wide apart, hold a barbell with a mixed grip, lift it by extending your hips and knees, then lower it back down.

name: Bulgarian Split Squat
instructions: Stand in a lunge position with your back foot elevated on a bench, lower your body until your front thigh is parallel to the floor, then stand back up.

name: Weighted Step-up
instructions: Stand in front of a bench or step, hold a dumbbell in each hand, step onto the bench, then step back down.

name: Swiss Ball Crunch
instructions: Lie back on a Swiss ball with your feet flat on the ground, perform a crunch by lifting your shoulders towards your hips.

name: Hanging Knee Raise
instructions: Hang from a pull-up bar, lift your knees towards your chest, then lower them back down.

name: Barbell Shrug
instructions: Hold a barbell with a shoulder-width grip, lift your shoulders towards your ears, then lower them back down.
